17:09.720 --> 17:10.789
Mr. Raker,

17:10.830 --> 17:11.819
in the background

17:11.860 --> 17:13.191
within earshot
of this interview?

17:13.230 --> 17:15.357
Uh...

17:15.400 --> 17:16.549
(exhales)
Looks like it.

17:16.600 --> 17:19.091
I-I don't remember.
And by, "We'll see you
in February,"

17:19.130 --> 17:21.234
did your coach mean
the next time you were playing

17:21.270 --> 17:23.158
against my client's team?

17:23.210 --> 17:24.404
I don't know,

17:24.440 --> 17:25.361
could have
meant anything, really.

17:25.410 --> 17:29.699
But didn't it mean this game
on February 15?

17:33.480 --> 17:35.118
I don't know.

17:35.150 --> 17:37.118
Maybe.

17:37.150 --> 17:39.084
I guess.

17:40.590 --> 17:42.512
KALINDA:
We've got a problem here.

17:42.560 --> 17:45.381
No, it's your neurologist friend
at Northwestern,

17:45.430 --> 17:48.627
Dr. Wedd, the one we want
to hire for the trial.

17:48.660 --> 17:50.662
He says he's never heard of you.

17:50.700 --> 17:51.564
He what?

17:51.600 --> 17:53.659
Yeah, he said he was
too busy to talk,

17:53.700 --> 17:55.565
and then he just rushed
out of the ofﬁce.

17:55.600 --> 17:57.306
You know what I think?

17:57.340 --> 17:59.103
Yeah,
'cause I'm thinking it, too.

17:59.140 --> 18:00.209
Canning got to him.

18:00.240 --> 18:01.207
Paid him off.

18:01.240 --> 18:02.673
Do we have a second-best option?

18:02.710 --> 18:04.701
No, not for hockey
impact studies.

18:04.750 --> 18:06.502
You may have another play.

18:06.550 --> 18:11.112
Given that I can't suggest
new legal strategy,

18:11.150 --> 18:13.311
I think you'll know
what I'm about to say.

18:13.360 --> 18:15.214
Find out
if Canning paid him off,

18:15.260 --> 18:16.659
and see if we can prove fraud.

18:16.690 --> 18:18.282
Obviously, I can't comment,

18:18.330 --> 18:19.786
but it sounds like you're
in movement.

18:19.830 --> 18:20.819
Iam.

18:20.860 --> 18:22.657
Following your
neurologist friend

18:22.700 --> 18:24.668
