writes a check to Obama's.

25:04.230 --> 25:07.290
Shall we drink to your allegedly
non-activist Supreme Court?

25:07.330 --> 25:11.539
Right. Scalia, Alito,
the rest of the big, scary five.

25:11.570 --> 25:13.572
Four.
We're wearing Kennedy down.

25:13.610 --> 25:15.202
All part of our clever
Highland Park

25:15.240 --> 25:16.901
liberal plan.

25:16.940 --> 25:19.545
Well, I would
love to stay

25:19.580 --> 25:20.808
and keep proving you wrong,

25:20.850 --> 25:22.215
but I've got
an early forensics class,

25:22.250 --> 25:25.117
and my instructor
here gets surly

25:25.150 --> 25:26.640
if we're late, so...

25:26.690 --> 25:28.214
It was nice meeting
you, Diane.

25:28.260 --> 25:29.955
And you, Miranda.
Keep breathing that fire.

25:29.990 --> 25:31.753
See you
tomorrow, Kurt.

25:31.790 --> 25:33.189
Yeah.

25:37.060 --> 25:39.790
(door opens and closes)

25:39.830 --> 25:41.229
Oh, she's wonderful.

25:41.270 --> 25:42.794
Crack shot, too.

25:42.840 --> 25:44.330
Crime labs will
be climbing

25:44.370 --> 25:46.065
all over each
other to hire her.

25:46.110 --> 25:48.078
So she's your...

25:48.110 --> 25:49.532
protge?

25:51.650 --> 25:54.210
You could call her that.

25:54.250 --> 25:57.947
Well, you two certainly
are of, uh, like minds.

25:57.990 --> 25:59.685
Except I like a
good argument.

25:59.720 --> 26:03.110
Consensus is less...

26:03.160 --> 26:04.718
interesting.

26:07.760 --> 26:09.318
Hello.

26:09.360 --> 26:11.863
(laughs)

26:11.900 --> 26:13.265
Is this a regular thing?

26:13.300 --> 26:17.134
Dropping in on men you
haven't seen in a year?

26:30.420 --> 26:32.285
I could use some direction here.

26:32.320 --> 26:36.313
Wh-What exactly
is this?

26:39.090 --> 26:41.650
It's me missing you.

26:41.700 --> 26:44.225
And hoping
you feel likewise.

26:52.840 --> 26:54.637
The real estate lady called.

26:54.680 --> 26:56.409
She thinks that they'll take
ten percent down.

26:56.440 --> 26:58.749
(chuckles)

26:58.780 --> 27:01.317
What?

27:01.350 --> 27:04.342
The real estate lady
should not be telling you that.

27:04.390 --> 27:06.711
She's calling here
because she wants

27:06.750 --> 27:08.354
to get you two excited
about the house.

27:08.390 --> 27:10.255
No, she was just
being nice.

27:10.290 --> 27:11.882
I'll talk to her.

27:11.930 --> 27:14.649
She should not
be calling here.

27:14.700 --> 27:16.827
You're really trying
to make it work, huh?

27:18.700 --> 27:20.668
I don't know.

27:23.140 --> 27:24.937
GRANT:
I-I knew

27:24.970 --> 27:26.403
they'd come after me.

27:26.440 --> 27:27.429
I was a marked man.

27:27.470 --> 27:29.404
JULIUS:
Because of your check
in that first game

27:29.440 --> 27:31.169
on their star,
Christian Lund?

27:31.210 --> 27:32.677
GRANT:
Yes.

27:32.710 --> 27:33.404
JULIUS:
Cameron Raker was
six-foot-three,

27:33.450 --> 27:36.010
225 pounds.

27:36.050 --> 27:37.347
How big were
you, Grant?

27:37.380 --> 27:39.314
GRANT:
Five-eleven, 190.

27:39.350 --> 27:40.385
JULIUS:
Yet, when he
goaded you,

27:40.420 --> 27:41.819
you fought him.

27:41.860 --> 27:43.088
I had no choice.

27:43.120 --> 27:44.985
If.... if I hadn't fought,
they would have gone

27:45.030 --> 27:46.827
after one of our
star players.

27:46.860 --> 27:48.020
How can you
be so sure?

27:48.060 --> 27:49.459
'Cause we would have done
the same thing.

27:49.500 --> 27:51.365
It's... it's the game.

27:51.400 --> 27:52.822
JULIUS:
No further questions.

27:52.870 --> 27:54.337
CANNING:
First, let me
start by saying

27:54.370 --> 27:57.430
how sorry I am about your recent
medical developments.

27:57.470 --> 28:00.405
If I can offer some advice
from personal experience:

28:00.440 --> 28:02.305
one day at a time.

28:02.340 --> 28:03.944
GRANT:
Thank you.

28:03.980 --> 28:07.143
So this baseline test
the doctor gave you

28:07.180 --> 28:09.740
at the start of the season--
did you fake yours?

28:10.850 --> 28:12.317
GRANT:
Uh...

28:12.350 --> 28:13.886
did-did I...?

28:13.920 --> 28:15.478
I'm-I-I don't...

28:15.520 --> 28:16.555
I'm not sure
I understand...

28:16.590 --> 28:18.820
Weren't you told by a teammate
to fake the test?

28:18.860 --> 28:20.896
You know, tap on the
keyboard a little slower

28:20.930 --> 28:23.455
or mix up the numbers
on the test grid.

28:23.500 --> 28:25.422
That way, if you suffered
a head injury during a game,

28:25.470 --> 28:27.392
the_team doctors would see
Similar results and clear you

28:27.430 --> 28:28.397
to play.
Objection.

28:28.440 --> 28:29.498
Hearsay.

28:29.540 --> 28:30.939
CANNING:
My apologies,
Your Honor.

28:30.970 --> 28:32.232
I should have
submitted this

28:32.270 --> 28:34.431
evidence deposition
from one Anthony Murillo,

28:34.480 --> 28:36.778
who was Mr. Duverney's roommate
during his rookie season.

28:36.810 --> 28:37.902
Mr. Duverney,

28:37.950 --> 28:39.508
one more time.

28:39.550 --> 28:41.347
Did you fake your baseline test?

28:48.120 --> 28:49.417
Yes.

28:49.460 --> 28:51.451
CANNING:
So, if you hadn't
faked your test,

28:51.490 --> 28:53.128
they would have been
able to diagnose you

28:53.160 --> 28:54.320
and treat you
properly.

28:54.360 --> 28:55.850
Objection--
beyond the witness's expertise.

28:55.900 --> 28:56.798
Withdrawn.

28:56.830 --> 28:58.366
No... no further questions,
Your Honor.

28:58.400 --> 29:02.188
Grant, why did you fake
your baseline test?

29:02.240 --> 29:04.800
For the same reason
a lot of players do:

29:04.840 --> 29:07.365
I was afraid of losing my job.

29:07.410 --> 29:08.809
What are you doing right now?

29:08.840 --> 29:10.535
Diane has me on something.
What do you need?

29:10.580 --> 29:13.401
How quickly can you upload
a video online?

29:13.450 --> 29:15.077
No fingerprints.

29:17.580 --> 29:19.218
(keyless lock chirps)

29:19.250 --> 29:21.354
CANNING:
Mrs. Florrick.

29:21.390 --> 29:24.484
My driver is still
at the dentist.

29:24.530 --> 29:26.054
Can I get a lift?

29:30.560 --> 29:33.028
How much flexibility
is there?

29:33.070 --> 29:34.799
Well, we offer
telecommuting.

29:34.840 --> 29:36.262
And then there's
day care at work.

29:36.300 --> 29:37.392
No, uh,

29:37.440 --> 29:38.862
I have an issue.

29:38.910 --> 29:40.468
My apartment has gone condo,

29:40.510 --> 29:42.876
and I have the possibility
of purchasing a house.

29:42.910 --> 29:45.003
And you need money
for the down payment?

29:45.050 --> 29:47.848
Yes, and a consistent
higher level in pay.

29:47.880 --> 29:50.371
I have private tuition, and I'm
trying to save for college.

29:51.420 --> 29:53.445
I'll work up an offer.

29:57.060 --> 29:58.584
No. No, I'm fine.

29:58.630 --> 30:00.894
Clearly, you're not fine,
or we wouldn't be sitting here.

30:00.930 --> 30:02.557
Mr. Canning,
seriously, I'm fine.

30:02.600 --> 30:04.067
All right,
let's leave it at this.

30:04.100 --> 30:05.567
I'll work up an offer.

30:05.600 --> 30:06.919
You'll think about it.

30:06.970 --> 30:08.835
We'll talk on the phone later.

30:08.870 --> 30:11.168
And that's it-- no pressure.

30:12.970 --> 30:15.575
Nobody's doing anything
wrong here, Alicia.

30:15.610 --> 30:18.306
This is how America works.

30:19.610 --> 30:21.316
(whistle blows)

30:21.350 --> 30:23.841
(heavy metal playing)

30:28.460 --> 30:29.950
ALICIA:
So you're familiar

30:29.990 --> 30:31.218
with this Web site?

30:31.260 --> 30:32.522
Yes. RinkFights.com.

30:32.560 --> 30:34.619
It's not sanctioned
by our league.

30:34.660 --> 30:36.628
Well, then, you're aware
that it lets fans vote

30:36.660 --> 30:38.161
on who will win the fight,

30:38.200 --> 30:40.464
that the players
actually have fight cards

30:40.500 --> 30:42.866
with win-loss records?
Yes.

30:42.900 --> 30:45.607
As APHL's chief
administrative officer,

30:45.640 --> 30:48.200
you have the final say
over league copyright issues,

30:48.240 --> 30:49.639
correct?
I do.

30:49.680 --> 30:52.604
The clips the Web site plays
are game broadcasts.

30:52.650 --> 30:54.072
Do you grant them permission
to use these?

30:54.120 --> 30:55.178
Absolutely not.

30:55.220 --> 30:58.587
As I said, this is not
an APHL-sanctioned Web site.

30:58.620 --> 31:00.588
Let's talk about another
Web site that uses your clips.

31:00.620 --> 31:01.985
(crowd cheering)

31:02.020 --> 31:03.282
ALICIA:
This is a recent

31:03.320 --> 31:04.628
Boston-Detroit game.

31:04.660 --> 31:06.059
It was posted
online yesterday

31:06.090 --> 31:07.921
by an employee
of our firm.

31:07.960 --> 31:10.554
Do you know how long it took
the Webmaster to receive

31:10.600 --> 31:12.420
a cease and desist order
from your office?

31:12.470 --> 31:13.596
No.

31:13.630 --> 31:15.234
Two hours.

31:15.270 --> 31:17.067
In the eight years
since RinkFights.com

31:17.100 --> 31:19.034
has been online,
how many

31:19.070 --> 31:22.130
cease and_desist letters
have you issued them?

31:22.180 --> 31:23.579
None.

31:23.610 --> 31:25.248
ALICIA:
Is that because
you encourage

31:25.280 --> 31:27.145
fans' enthusiasm
for fights?

31:27.180 --> 31:28.909
No, of course not.
Then why aren't you

31:28.950 --> 31:30.349
removing
these fight videos?

31:30.380 --> 31:32.211
Well, I guess we'll start.

31:32.250 --> 31:33.512
Thank you for the
encouragement.

31:33.550 --> 31:35.586
And thank you
for that damaging testimony.

31:35.620 --> 31:36.655
Objection.

31:36.690 --> 31:38.487
Sustained.

31:47.130 --> 31:49.269
I think we should all
have a little sit-down.

31:49.300 --> 31:50.938
About?

31:50.970 --> 31:53.234
Me helping you win this thing.

31:59.080 --> 32:01.617
The truth--
are you in bed with him?

32:03.380 --> 32:05.211
Am I in bed with him?

32:05.250 --> 32:07.684
Yeah. That's what I've been
hearing from unnamed sources.

32:07.720 --> 32:10.951
I can neither confirm nor deny
that we have

32:10.990 --> 32:13.652
any formal agreement
with Frank Michael Thomas.

32:13.690 --> 32:17.968
And you don't think suits
like yours and Mr. Thomas's

32:18.000 --> 32:19.729
will hurt the sport
of ice hockey?

32:19.770 --> 32:21.692
No. Is fighting essential
to the sport of ice hockey?

32:21.740 --> 32:23.264
Some think it's a safety valve.

32:23.300 --> 32:25.006
Without it,
you'd see a lot more sticks

32:25.040 --> 32:26.701
swinging out there.
Not in college hockey.

32:26.740 --> 32:28.628
Not in the Olympics.
You would get ejected.

32:28.680 --> 32:30.705
But aren't the stakes
a little higher in the pros?

32:30.740 --> 32:32.139
Players' livelihoods
are on the line.

32:32.180 --> 32:34.011
Then why are there
no real fights

32:34.050 --> 32:35.369
during the championship series?

32:37.780 --> 32:39.680
Sounds like your
closing argument.

32:39.720 --> 32:41.711
Thanks.
No problem.

32:41.760 --> 32:44.729
If you need any more,
you should talk to Julius.

32:46.730 --> 32:48.049
So you were in London, right?

32:48.100 --> 32:50.125
Setting up
your magazine's operation

32:50.160 --> 32:51.593
for the Olympics?

32:51.630 --> 32:53.063
Yes.

32:53.100 --> 32:54.658
How was it?

32:54.700 --> 32:58.704
Rainy. You slept with Will
after I left town, didn't you?

33:01.040 --> 33:02.473
I promise you

33:02.510 --> 33:03.738
he didn't tell me.

33:03.780 --> 33:05.668
Will didn't put up
much of a fight

33:05.710 --> 33:08.372
when I told him
about the London offer.

33:08.420 --> 33:11.548
And then I e-mailed
him right after I got
there, but no response.

33:11.590 --> 33:13.478
I chalked it up to
his being so busy,

33:13.520 --> 33:15.158
but Will never
not responds.

33:15.190 --> 33:19.229
I knew you two
had history, so...

33:19.260 --> 33:21.296
two plus two.

33:24.200 --> 33:27.169
I think that's a conversation
you should have With Will.

33:30.700 --> 33:31.701
You're right.

33:31.740 --> 33:33.503
Inappropriate of me.

33:34.840 --> 33:35.875
You know,

33:35.910 --> 33:39.539
for the record, it wasn't over
between Will and I

33:39.580 --> 33:41.548
when I left for London.

33:41.580 --> 33:44.344
Then you slept with him,
and it was over.

34:07.810 --> 34:09.675
We appreciate
the change of heart.

34:09.710 --> 34:12.543
We could use whatever
help you can give us.

34:12.580 --> 34:15.413
Shouldn't we wait
for Ms. Lockhart

34:15.450 --> 34:16.712
before getting
to brass tacks?

34:16.750 --> 34:17.842
I understood
she was gonna

34:17.880 --> 34:19.381
be a part of this.

34:19.420 --> 34:21.718
Diane got pulled away
on another case.

34:21.760 --> 34:24.354
But we'll bring her
up to speed.
So be it.

34:24.390 --> 34:27.188
Don't look at this

34:27.230 --> 34:29.790
as a benevolent gesture--
I just think you folks did

34:29.830 --> 34:31.866
a hell of a job
in court today,

34:31.900 --> 34:35.336
and it looks like helping
you might actually
help me after all.

34:35.370 --> 34:37.759
Um, I'm sorry, would
you excuse me, please?

34:37.800 --> 34:39.131
Of course.

34:39.170 --> 34:41.638
Now, you just
promise me this--

34:41.680 --> 34:43.773
when you use this
against Louis Canning,

34:43.810 --> 34:47.075
try to draw blood.

34:48.320 --> 34:50.618
We're adding a witness,
Dr. Andr Wedd.

34:50.650 --> 34:53.210
And you're telling me
in accordance to court rules.

34:53.250 --> 34:55.457
Very honorable of you.
Dr. Wedd is a
neurologist...

34:55.490 --> 34:56.809
Who has repeatedly
lambasted the league

34:56.860 --> 34:58.555
for its approach
to head injuries.

34:58.590 --> 34:59.887
I've read
all his articles.

34:59.930 --> 35:02.125
He has a unique gift
for repeating himself.

35:02.160 --> 35:03.058
What Dr. Wedd is

35:03.100 --> 35:04.863
testifying to isn't in
any of his articles.

35:04.900 --> 35:06.458
Really?

35:06.500 --> 35:08.138
Dr. Wedd approached
theleague

35:08.170 --> 35:10.161
with a rigorous protocol
for evaluating and treating

35:10.200 --> 35:11.838
players with
head injuries--

35:11.870 --> 35:15.135
one that wouldn't _scare
players into faking
baseline tests.

35:15.180 --> 35:17.831
Had the league not dismissed
Dr. Wedd so quickly,

35:17.880 --> 35:21.270
Grant Duverney would
have been properly
diagnosed and treated.

35:21.320 --> 35:23.345
I can show you the
rejection e-mail

35:23.380 --> 35:25.780
that Dr. Wedd received
from the league VP.

35:25.820 --> 35:27.811
It's a quick read.

35:29.860 --> 35:32.749
I'll run it by the league,

35:34.800 --> 35:36.153
Oh.

35:36.200 --> 35:38.191
One more thing.

35:39.400 --> 35:40.697
You have 24 hours.

35:45.340 --> 35:47.763
DIANE:
Fishing?

35:47.810 --> 35:48.879
McVEIGH:
At Horsetail Lake.

35:48.910 --> 35:50.434
It's an easy drive
from the city.

35:50.480 --> 35:51.947
We'd make it a day trip.

35:51.980 --> 35:52.878
Kurt, have we met?

35:52.910 --> 35:54.411
I'll do all the baiting.

35:54.450 --> 35:55.872
Oh, would you
have it any other way?

35:55.920 --> 35:57.649
We pack a lunch,
we rent a boat,

35:57.680 --> 35:59.443
and we breathe something
other than car exhaust

35:59.490 --> 36:01.651
for a few hours,
and the good news for you--

36:01.690 --> 36:02.952
cell phone coverage.

36:02.990 --> 36:05.458
(phone rings)
(laughs)
Hold on a second.

36:05.490 --> 36:07.287
JACK:
You don't hate me,
Hello?

36:07.330 --> 36:09.298
right?

36:09.330 --> 36:10.957
Uh, Jack?

36:11.000 --> 36:11.819
Uh, hello.

36:11.870 --> 36:14.338
I said I'd take you out
some other time,

36:14.370 --> 36:17.635
so I'm calling
to find out that other time.

36:17.670 --> 36:18.967
Uh... when do you

36:19.010 --> 36:19.965
have in mind?

36:20.010 --> 36:21.477
I was thinking Friday night.

36:21.510 --> 36:22.909
Unwind after work.

36:22.940 --> 36:26.671
I, uh... Can you
hold on a second?

36:26.710 --> 36:27.802
Kurt?

36:27.850 --> 36:29.670
No, Jack.
Oh, hold on a second.

36:29.720 --> 36:30.812
Um...

36:30.850 --> 36:31.782
Who's Kurt?

36:31.820 --> 36:34.880
He's j... he's just
a-a business associate.

36:34.920 --> 36:37.480
Uh, I-I will be
right back, uh...

36:37.520 --> 36:39.351
Jack.
Jack. Hold on.

36:39.390 --> 36:41.551
Hello?

36:41.600 --> 36:43.659
Look, if Horsetail Lake
doesn't cut it for you, then...

36:43.700 --> 36:44.860
No, no, no. It sounds fun.

36:44.900 --> 36:47.562
When were you... thinking?

36:47.600 --> 36:49.830
Saturday morning.
Pick you up at 8:00.

36:49.870 --> 36:53.533
Perfect.
I will see you then. Bye.

36:53.570 --> 36:54.776
Still there?

36:54.810 --> 36:56.334
Yep.

36:56.380 --> 36:57.870
Friday night sounds good.

37:01.650 --> 37:03.345
ELI:
It's pretty darn hard

37:03.380 --> 37:05.644
being on the outside
looking in, huh?

37:05.690 --> 37:08.955
I'm just sitting here watching
the wheels turn round and round.

37:08.990 --> 37:10.958
What do you need, Eli?

37:10.990 --> 37:13.481
I did not leak to the
disciplinary board.

37:13.530 --> 37:15.657
But you're gonna
tell me who did?

37:15.700 --> 37:16.997
I can tell you
my suspicions.

37:17.030 --> 37:19.294
David Lee.
Yup.

37:19.330 --> 37:20.866
(quiet chuckle)
That's funny.

37:20.900 --> 37:22.561
David Lee was
in here yesterday

37:22.600 --> 37:24.830
saying you leaked it.

37:25.870 --> 37:27.906
He did not.

37:27.940 --> 37:29.476
He did.
No.

37:29.510 --> 37:31.307
No, you're playing us
against each other.

37:31.350 --> 37:33.306
As long as we're
fighting each other,

37:33.350 --> 37:34.612
you're safe.

37:34.650 --> 37:38.484
I don't think
I'll ever be... safe.

37:38.520 --> 37:40.647
It's good talking
to you, Eli.

37:45.960 --> 37:48.326
Excuse me, Diane?

37:49.500 --> 37:51.661
Uh, yes, Alicia?

37:54.070 --> 37:56.664
I have received
a formal job offer

37:56.700 --> 37:58.565
from Louis Canning.

37:58.610 --> 38:00.032
From Canning?

38:00.070 --> 38:02.607
He approached me
several months ago
and I declined,

38:02.640 --> 38:04.403
but he's been persistent.

38:04.450 --> 38:05.747
And you're considering it?

38:05.780 --> 38:07.873
I'd like to stay,
but his offer...

38:07.910 --> 38:09.969
would go a long way
to helping me

38:10.020 --> 38:12.318
cover a mortgage payment.
It wasn't Louis Canning

38:12.350 --> 38:15.888
who gave you a chance after
13 years away from the law.

38:19.390 --> 38:20.880
This is his offer.

38:20.930 --> 38:22.625
If I stay at the firm,

38:22.660 --> 38:24.821
it has to be more.

38:28.800 --> 38:32.463
You'll give me till
the end ON the week?
0.

38:32.510 --> 38:35.308
I can't.

38:36.740 --> 38:39.504
Yep, everybody changes.

38:39.550 --> 38:43.509
End of the week, Alicia,
or you can clean out
your desk right now.

38:52.430 --> 38:55.524
You've heard nothing?
No text, no e-mail, nothing.

38:55.560 --> 38:57.858
I would've thought Canning
would want to end this,

38:57.900 --> 39:00.664
keep the league from
getting skewered in court.

39:00.700 --> 39:02.930
Fine, put Dr. Wedd
on the stand.
Mr. Cain,

39:02.970 --> 39:05.359
do you have a minute?
Can it wait until
after court?

39:05.410 --> 39:07.037
There is no court.

39:07.070 --> 39:08.970
I just spoke
to Judge Rigby.

39:09.010 --> 39:11.604
The Snow Plain Corporation
has reevaluated its position

39:11.650 --> 39:13.106
on the original case.

39:13.150 --> 39:14.845
We're now prepared to settle.

39:14.880 --> 39:18.418
W-Well, we're way beyond
that point, Mr. Hines.

39:18.450 --> 39:21.010
The only acceptable number
is the full $5 million.

39:21.050 --> 39:24.110
Good. Because that's
what we're offering.

39:24.160 --> 39:27.049
Talk to your client
and let me know.

39:30.500 --> 39:32.491
What just happened?

39:32.530 --> 39:35.966
I think we just won.

39:36.000 --> 39:38.139
(loud, overlapping chatter)

39:38.170 --> 39:40.707
No! No, no, no, no!

39:40.740 --> 39:41.775
No bonus!

39:41.810 --> 39:43.129
She just won
a case.

39:43.180 --> 39:45.705
Alicia did not
Win a case--
she was handed

39:45.750 --> 39:47.877
a settlement.
Which we wouldn't have gotten
but for her performance.

39:47.910 --> 39:50.140
Oh, forgive me, Miyagi,
I forgot who was guiding Alicia.

39:50.180 --> 39:53.684
And since when do you have
a problem with winning
money for clients?

39:53.720 --> 39:55.415
Oh, who cares
about the client! Will!

39:55.460 --> 39:57.155
Tell them how disastrous
it would be if Alicia walks.

39:57.190 --> 39:58.851
JULIUS:
I don't care
what she's paid.

39:58.890 --> 40:01.529
I just can't afford to lose
another body right now.

40:01.560 --> 40:02.788
Look, we all
know the issue.

40:02.830 --> 40:05.162
Why don't we just
put it to a vote.

40:05.200 --> 40:07.498
All those in favor.
No.

40:07.530 --> 40:10.465
She's getting her bonus.

40:10.500 --> 40:12.434
I'm invoking
managing-partner prerogative.

40:12.470 --> 40:14.199
You can't be serious.

40:14.240 --> 40:16.708
Mm, what are we talking about?
WILL:
The firm's bylaws

40:16.740 --> 40:18.947
allow the managing partner
to act unilaterally.

40:18.980 --> 40:20.504
Under extenuating
circumstances.

40:20.550 --> 40:22.142
We must have
missed the memo.

40:22.180 --> 40:24.614
Apparently, we're now
Stalin & Associates.

40:24.650 --> 40:26.584
Well, if it means
Alicia sticks around,

40:26.620 --> 40:27.917
I second it.
You can't second it.

40:27.950 --> 40:29.451
The matter is closed.

40:29.490 --> 40:31.958
Any other business?

40:35.960 --> 40:38.895
You just stuck your neck out
for a third-year associate.

40:38.930 --> 40:41.194
Your suspension has
left us exposed.

40:41.230 --> 40:44.768
I stuck my neck out for
the future of this firm.

40:44.810 --> 40:46.766
Hi.

40:46.810 --> 40:51.509
(chuckles) I'm not sure what
time I can get out tonight.

40:51.550 --> 40:53.541
(laughing)

40:56.120 --> 40:59.248
(muffled talking)

40:59.290 --> 41:01.679
(laughing)

41:03.820 --> 41:05.959
But thank you very
much, Mr. Canning.

41:08.290 --> 41:10.497
Is something wrong?

41:11.700 --> 41:13.122
You used me.

41:13.170 --> 41:15.195
No.

41:15.240 --> 41:17.800
The firm made it attractive
for me to stay.

41:17.840 --> 41:20.809
It was unexpected.
Unexpected as
a knife in the back.

41:23.010 --> 41:24.898
Y... You should
still be pleased.

41:24.950 --> 41:26.770
You did well for your client.

41:26.810 --> 41:28.812
Whatever deal you
cut with Snow Plain

41:28.850 --> 41:30.875
deflects any liability
away from the league.

41:30.920 --> 41:32.012
No, I'm pleased--

41:32.050 --> 41:34.587
because I needed to smoke
Frank Michael Thomas out,

41:34.620 --> 41:36.759
find out what he had
for his class action.

41:36.790 --> 41:39.179
And thanks to your good
lawyering, now I know,

41:39.230 --> 41:40.879
and I'll be
ready for him.

41:40.930 --> 41:43.751
So I guess what I want
to say to you, Alicia,

41:43.800 --> 41:45.199
is thank you.

41:45.230 --> 41:46.720
Thank you.

41:52.070 --> 41:53.901
(quiet sigh)

41:56.610 --> 41:59.704
Anything you have
would be really helpful.

41:59.750 --> 42:01.103
Okay. Okay, good.

42:01.150 --> 42:02.777
Thanks.

42:04.950 --> 42:07.817
The other day when
you brought the beer,

42:07.850 --> 42:10.057
I wasn't...
It's all right.

42:10.090 --> 42:11.819
They were warm, aanay.

42:13.690 --> 42:14.952
(sighs)

42:15.000 --> 42:17.651
Look, I can't go back
to the way it was before.

42:17.700 --> 42:18.928
There's just been too much.

42:18.970 --> 42:21.791
I know.

42:21.840 --> 42:22.932
But...

42:22.970 --> 42:26.303
I'd like to try
to make it work.

42:29.640 --> 42:32.245
It's just that everything...

42:32.280 --> 42:34.305
it has to be...

42:34.350 --> 42:35.942
on the table.

42:35.980 --> 42:39.643
I can't be the only
one being forthcoming.

42:39.690 --> 42:43.182
I can't be the only
one being honest.

42:44.220 --> 42:46.825
Can... you do that?

42:49.630 --> 42:51.052
Yeah.

42:54.200 --> 42:55.895
Okay.

42:57.070 --> 43:00.130
I'll see you tomorrow.

